    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-03-10T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-03-10T23:00:00-05:00" n="373"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d373">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/2968: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Josselyn</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-03-11T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 11, 1938—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received March 12—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reference Peiping’s February 26, 4 p.m.,<note n="81" xml:id="d373fn81">Not
                        printed.</note> to the Embassy Hankow repeating Tokyo’s February 26, 1 p.m.
                    I have received copy of notice in English dropped by Japanese planes at
                    Chengchow February 27 reading as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The Commander of Japanese Army advise the foreign gentlemen and ladies
                            you must take off the Chinese trains at neighborhood of the foreigners’
                            houses until 28th in this month. Unless you do not take off the Chinese
                            trains on the railway Japanese troops will bomb them from 1st of March.
                            At that time Japan Government cannot assume responsibility for any
                            danger.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Josselyn</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
